tool_sequence.description: Searched "volume from pressure, temperature, mass" on Google.
Opened the "Specific Volume: Definition, Formulas, Examples - ThoughtCo" page.
Searched "joules to atm" on Google and noted the conversion of 1 Joule = 0.0098692326671601 Liter Atmosphere from the featured text snippet.
Plugged numbers into the ideal gas equation: V = (0.08205736608096 L-atm/K-mol * 277.039K * 2.58 mol) / (1071.7245 atm) = 0.05473 L.

parsed_steps.original_text: Searched "volume from pressure, temperature, mass" on Google.
Opened the "Specific Volume: Definition, Formulas, Examples - ThoughtCo" page.
Noted that PV = nRT where V is volume, R is the ideal gas constant, T is temperature, P is pressure, and M is moles.
Followed the "gas constant" link.
Noted that R = 8.31446261815324 J/K-mol.
Searched "Freon-12" on Google.
Opened the "Dichlorodifluoromethane" on Wikipedia.
Noted the molar mass of 120.91 g/mol.
Converted 0.312 kg = 312 g.
Calculated moles: 312 g / 120.91 g/mol = 2.58 mol.
Searched "Marianas Trench pressure" on Google.
Noted the pressure in the featured text snippet of 15,750 psi.
Searched "psi to atm" on Google.
Noted 1 psi = 0.068046 atm.
Converted psi to atm: 15,750 * 0.068046 = 1071.7245 atm.
Searched "Marianas Trench temperature" on Google.
Noted the temperature range from 34-39F.
Searched "F to K" on Google.
Noted that K equals F plus 459.67 times 5/9 from the conversion tool.
Converted temperature to K: 39 + 459.67 * 5/9 = 277.039K.
Searched "joules to atm" on Google and noted the conversion of 1 Joule = 0.0098692326671601 Liter Atmosphere from the featured text snippet.
Changed PV = nRT to V = nRT/P
Plugged numbers into the ideal gas equation: V = (0.08205736608096 L-atm/K-mol * 277.039K * 2.58 mol) / (1071.7245 atm) = 0.05473 L.
Converted to mL: 0.05473 L = 54.
Rounded to the nearest mL.
